  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Press Council Indonesia - Democratic dialogue in 140 characters</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a research-based minor study project, which will be conducted in collaboration between The Press Council of Indonesia (overall responsible) and the research institution Indonesia Indicator, with possible involvement of democracy experts from other institutions. The aim is to examine how the proliferation of and access to social media in a newly democratised country impacts political participation &amp; dialogue with a case study of 2014 Presidential election. The purpose is to provide a deeper understanding of the potential development impacts (opportunities and potential challenges) of the increasing role of social media in young democracies. 
The project period is 6 months expected to finish in April/May 2015. Total budget is DKK 600,000.</narrative>
  </description>
